      "name": "Wooden skewers",
      "amount": "12",
      "notes": "soaked in water for 30 minutes"
    }
  ],
  "instructions": [
    "Preheat a grill or grill pan to medium-high heat.",
    "Thread a slice of Parma ham, a few mint leaves, and a few basil leaves onto each skewer.",
    "Brush the skewers with olive oil and season with garlic powder, salt, and black pepper.",
    "Grill the skewers for 2-3 minutes per side, or until the Parma ham is crispy.",
    "Serve the skewers hot with a squeeze of lime juice.",
    "Garnish with additional mint and basil leaves, if desired.",
    "Steam the skewers for an additional 2 minutes, if desired, for a lighter texture.",
    "Serve immediately and enjoy."
  ],
